1 'BOAT' 'BOATS'~
In some areas with a rather large body of water, it is possible that some
depths can be rather, well, deep.  And unless you can breathe through water,
you're going to drown.  To rectify this, and hold onto your precious life, you
must get ahold of a boat. Beg, borrow, or steal one, then hold onto it by
"hold boat" and go ahead and move about.  Just be careful of currents and
wind in some cases.
~

101 BODYBAG~
Syntax: &Wbodybag <name> <bag/yes>
          bodybag <name> will show the status of the corpse.
&w
BODYBAG gets all of <character's> corpses and puts them in your inventory
to do with as you wish.

If you find yourself getting the wrong corpse, post a bug report immediately!
See also TIMER
~

1 BOT BOTS BOTTING~
Bots, the running of a character using triggers while there is no one
attending it, is not illegal in itself. However, bots are held to the
same rules as playing characters. See Laws regarding "staking" and
other applicable laws. The character is accountable for any act the
bot commits.
~

1 'BP'~
This is an abbreviation for blood points.  Vampires begin with 10 bp
at creation and gain 1/1 bp for each subsequent level.
~

1 BRANDISH QUAFF RECITE ZAP~
Syntax:  brandish                       (to invoke a staff)
Syntax:  quaff  <potion>                (to quaff potions)
         quaff  <potion> <container>    (quaff directly from container)
Syntax:  recite <scroll> <target>       (to recite a scroll)
Syntax:  zap    <target>                (to use a wand on a target)
 
BRANDISH invokes a magical staff.
 
QUAFF quaffs a potion (as opposed to DRINK, which drinks mundane liquids).
 
RECITE recites a magical scroll; the <target> is optional, depending on the
nature of the scroll.
 
ZAP fires a magical wand at a target.  If the target is not specified, and
you are fighting someone, then that character is used for a target.
 
You must be holding a wand or a staff before using BRANDISH or ZAP.
 
All of these commands use up their objects:  Potions and scrolls have a
single charge.  Wands and staves (staffs) have multiple charges.  When a
magical object has no more charges, it will be consumed.  Use the spell
'identify' to see the remaining charges.
 
See EAT, BACKFIRE, RECHARGE
~

1 BROACH~
Syntax:  broach <direction>
 
This skill causes the vampire to attempt to bypass a locked or barred
door or other obstruction.
 
~

101 BUILDING~
Building requirements:
minimum 3 lines, as long as the ---- in the online editor or as possible, your
choice.
Don't assume a player is coming from a specific direction or has come across
a mob, object, or room prior to that one, unless you have taken absolutly every
precaution to assure it happens that way.
Don't assume on weather or time of day.  It may be hot or cold, and the
sun is not necessarily high in the sky and shining bright, it could be
at night time.  We now have nightdescrtiptions for this, read help NITEDESC.
Try not to get repetitive with your descs, it is not easy to write a multi-
hundred room area, but that's part of the job.  It is creative writing, so be
creative, maybe pick up that old highschool grammar/english book...
We are mideavil.  Using a name like Galactica may get you butt-raped by Puff.
Don't do like Merlin!  Take into consideration ceratin applicable laws of
nature.  A room on a second floor usually has to have one underneath it on the
first...  Also, remember REDIT FLAGS INDOORS so it doesn't rain in a house.

If you'd like to read more of my ramblings (and being molested by Puff) read
help IMMORTAL and CLANHEAD, GUILDHEAD, COUNCILHEAD, or see wizhelp.
~

